<p>Avery Kolers, Professor and Department Chair of Philosophy at the <a href="https://artsandsciences.louisville.edu/academics-programs/academic-departments/philosophy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">University of Louisville</a>, will be moving to the <a href="https://philosophy.utk.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">University of Tennessee</a> Department of Philosophy, where he will be Professor and Department Chair. <span id="more-54497"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-54498 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/kolers-avery-photo.png" alt="" width="673" height="400" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/kolers-avery-photo.png 2026w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/kolers-avery-photo-300x178.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/kolers-avery-photo-1024x609.png 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/kolers-avery-photo-768x456.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/kolers-avery-photo-1536x913.png 1536w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/kolers-avery-photo-400x238.png 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 673px) 100vw, 673px" /></p>
<p><a href="https://louisville.edu/faculty/ahkole01" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Professor Kolers</a> works in social and political philosophy and ethics. He is the author of <em>A Moral Theory of Solidarity </em>(2016) and <em>Land, Conflict, and Justice: A Political Theory of Territory </em>(2009), among other works, which you can learn more about <a href="https://philpeople.org/profiles/avery-kolers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
<p>He takes up his new position at the University of Tennessee in January, 2026.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/08/04/kolers-from-louisville-to-tennessee/">Kolers from Louisville to Tennessee</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>